<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>9987</anchor> <rss>erct-002G.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002G</addr>  <route>erct-002G.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">Contractible maps</link> are <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retractions</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002G.agda" type="external">erct-002G.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible map</link> <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>9988</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>; we define a section <tex>s \colon  B \to  A</tex> to take <tex>b:B</tex> to the first component of the centre of contraction of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex>. The witness <tex>h_s \colon  f \circ  s \sim   1_{ B }</tex> exhibiting <tex>s</tex> as a section of <tex>f</tex>, we use the second component of the centre of contraction.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>9989</anchor> <rss>erct-003A.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>erct-003A</addr>  <route>erct-003A.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>1</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Relating different kinds of equivalence</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>9990</anchor> <rss>erct-002E.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002E</addr>  <route>erct-002E.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">Invertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002E.agda" type="external">erct-002E.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>9991</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Let <tex>\epsilon   \colon  f \circ  f ^{-1}  =  1_{ B }</tex> be the counit of the <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">inverse</link> to <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex>. Given <tex>b:B</tex>, we must show that the fiber of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>; the centre of contraction is given by the pair <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( f ^{-1}  x,  \epsilon  x \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>, and the required paths can be constructed via the <link href="erct-001R.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001R" title="Path object structure on fibers">univalence principle for fibers</link> using the unit <tex>\eta \colon  f ^{-1} \circ  f =  1_{ A }</tex>, the coherence <tex>\chi \colon   \mathsf {act}_{ f } \circ \eta \sim \epsilon \circ  f</tex>, and the <link href="erct-001V.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001V" title="Naturality of homotopies">naturality of homotopies</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>9992</anchor> <rss>erct-002F.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002F</addr>  <route>erct-002F.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">Contractible maps</link> are <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002F.agda" type="external">erct-002F.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible map</link> <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>9993</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>; we define a retraction <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex> to take <tex>b:B</tex> to the first component of the centre of contraction of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex>. To construct <tex>h_r \colon  r \circ  f \sim   1_{ A }</tex> exhibiting <tex>r</tex> as a retraction of <tex>f</tex>, we use the identification between any two elements of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>fx</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>9994</anchor> <rss>erct-002G.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002G</addr>  <route>erct-002G.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">Contractible maps</link> are <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retractions</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002G.agda" type="external">erct-002G.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible map</link> <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>9995</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>; we define a section <tex>s \colon  B \to  A</tex> to take <tex>b:B</tex> to the first component of the centre of contraction of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex>. The witness <tex>h_s \colon  f \circ  s \sim   1_{ B }</tex> exhibiting <tex>s</tex> as a section of <tex>f</tex>, we use the second component of the centre of contraction.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>9996</anchor> <rss>erct-002H.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002H</addr>  <route>erct-002H.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">Contractible maps</link> are <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002H.agda" type="external">erct-002H.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible map</link> <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>9997</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Because <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible maps</link> are both <link href="erct-002F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002F" title="Contractible maps are sections">sections</link> and <link href="erct-002G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002G" title="Contractible maps are retractions">retractions</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>9998</anchor> <rss>erct-002M.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002M</addr>  <route>erct-002M.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">Quasi-invertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002M.agda" type="external">erct-002M.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-invertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>9999</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Any <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> <link href="erct-002C.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002C" title="From quasi-inverses to coherent inverses">can be improved</link> to a <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">coherent inverse</link>, and <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">any coherently invertible map</link> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10000</anchor> <rss>erct-002N.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002N</addr>  <route>erct-002N.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">Biinvertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002N.agda" type="external">erct-002N.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">biinvertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10001</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>As <link href="erct-002D.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002D" title="From biinverses to quasi-inverses">biinvertible maps are quasi-invertible</link> and <link href="erct-002M.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002M" title="Quasi-invertible maps are contractible">quasi-invertible maps are contractible</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10002</anchor> <rss>erct-002O.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002O</addr>  <route>erct-002O.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Pushforward along <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> maps</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002O.agda" type="external">erct-002O.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>; then for any type <tex>C</tex>, the postcomposition map <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( f \circ  - \right ) \mathclose {} \colon   \mathopen {} \left ( C \to  A \right ) \mathclose {} \to   \mathopen {} \left ( C \to  B \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10003</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>The <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section and retraction</link> are built using by postcomposing with the designated <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section and retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex>; the witnesses for the postcomposition <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">sections and retractions</link> are constructed using the <link href="erct-0015.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0015" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">univalence principle for function spaces</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10004</anchor> <rss>erct-002P.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002P</addr>  <route>erct-002P.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Restriction along <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> maps</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002P.agda" type="external">erct-002P.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>; then for any type <tex>C</tex>, the precomposition map <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( - \circ  f \right ) \mathclose {} \colon   \mathopen {} \left ( B \to  C \right ) \mathclose {} \to \mathopen {} \left ( A \to  C \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10005</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Analogous to the corresponding result for <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">pushforward along biinvertible maps</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10006</anchor> <rss>erct-002W.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002W</addr>  <route>erct-002W.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">Biinvertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002W.agda" type="external">erct-002W.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible map</link> <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10007</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>We must show that each <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> is a <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">proposition</link>; in fact, each <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> is <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">contractible</link> as <link href="erct-002N.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002N" title="Biinvertible maps are contractible">biinvertible maps are contractible</link>, and <link href="erct-001K.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001K" title="Contractible types are propositions">contractible types are propositions</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10008</anchor> <rss>erct-002X.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002X</addr>  <route>erct-002X.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">Biinvertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjective</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0029.agda" type="external">erct-0029.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjective</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10009</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>This is immediate, using the unit map of <link href="erct-0028.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0028" title="Propositional truncation">propositional truncation</link> and the <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">section</link> of <tex>f</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10010</anchor> <rss>erct-002Y.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002Y</addr>  <route>erct-002Y.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">Bijections</link> are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002Y.agda" type="external">erct-002Y.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijection</link> <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10011</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Fixing <tex>b:B</tex>, we must check that the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>. For the centre of contraction, we must construct an element of this <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link>; because <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link>, the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, so it suffices by the induction principle for <link href="erct-0028.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0028" title="Propositional truncation">propositional truncation</link> to observe that the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> is <em>inhabited</em> because <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjective</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10012</anchor> <rss>erct-002Z.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002Z</addr>  <route>erct-002Z.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">Bijections</link> are <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002Z.agda" type="external">erct-002Z.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijection</link> <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10013</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By <ref addr="erct-002Y" href="erct-002Y.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>, <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijections</link> are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>; by <ref addr="erct-002H" href="erct-002H.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>, <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijections</link> are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10014</anchor> <rss>erct-003H.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-003H</addr>  <route>erct-003H.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>10</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">Biinvertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijective</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003H.agda" type="external">erct-003H.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijection</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10015</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>10</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>   </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By <ref addr="erct-002W" href="erct-002W.xml" taxon="Lemma"/> and <ref addr="erct-002X" href="erct-002X.xml" taxon="Lemma"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10016</anchor> <rss>erct-001T.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001T</addr>  <route>erct-001T.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> map</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001T.agda" type="external">erct-001T.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is called <em><strong><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span></strong></em> when all of its <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fibers</link> are <link href="erct-001G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001G" title="N-truncated type"><span style="white-space: nowrap"><tex>n</tex>-truncated</span> types</link>. By analogy, we shall also refer to maps as <em><strong>contractible</strong></em> when their fibers are; we shall refer to maps as <em><strong>propositional</strong></em> when their fibers are <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">propositions</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10017</anchor> <rss>erct-001Q.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001Q</addr>  <route>erct-001Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Fiber</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001Q.agda" type="external">erct-001Q.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The <em><strong>fiber</strong></em> of a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> at an element <tex>b:B</tex> is the type consisting of elements <tex>a \colon  A</tex> equipped with identifications <tex>p \colon  fa=b</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10018</anchor> <rss>erct-000Y.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000Y</addr>  <route>erct-000Y.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Section-retraction pair</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000Y.agda" type="external">erct-000Y.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>s  \colon  B  \to  A</tex> and <tex>r  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be a pair of maps. A homotopy <tex>h  \colon  r \circ  s  \sim   1_{ B }</tex> exhibits <tex>s</tex> as a <em><strong>section</strong></em> of <tex>r</tex> and <tex>r</tex> as a <em><strong>retraction</strong></em> of <tex>s</tex>. Together, <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( s,r \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> are referred to as a <em><strong>section-retraction pair</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10019</anchor> <rss>erct-002H.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002H</addr>  <route>erct-002H.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">Contractible maps</link> are <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002H.agda" type="external">erct-002H.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible map</link> <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10020</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-002H</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Because <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible maps</link> are both <link href="erct-002F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002F" title="Contractible maps are sections">sections</link> and <link href="erct-002G.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002G" title="Contractible maps are retractions">retractions</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>